"{\n  \"correct\": \"no\",\n  \"explanation\": \"The code is setting both the major locator and the xticks manually. The major locator is set to MonthLocator, which will try to set the ticks to the start of each month. However, the xticks are also set manually to the unique dates in the dataframe, which can conflict with the MonthLocator. This can result in the dates not being displayed correctly on the x-axis.\",\n  \"patch\": \"17,18c17\\n< ax.set_xticks(df.date.unique())\\n< ax.set_xticklabels(labels=df.date.unique(), rotation=45)\\n---\\n> # Removed manual xticks setting to let MonthLocator handle it\"\n}"